3 nest_with_margins() and nest_by_with_margins()






Only works with a local data frame



nest_with_margins() and nest_by_with_margins() only works with a local data frame, as most lazy tables do not support nest operations.



3.1 Usage
nest_with_magins() and nest_by_with_magins() have similar behaviour. Each function nests for each group.

nest_with_magins() returns an ungrouped data frame, like tidyr::nest().
nest_by_with_magins() returns a row-wise data frame, like dplyr::nest_by().


df1 |&gt;
  nest_with_margins(
    .margins = c(cat, subcat)
  )

# A tibble: 8 × 3
  cat   subcat data            
  &lt;fct&gt; &lt;ord&gt;  &lt;list&gt;          
1 (all) (all)  &lt;tibble [8 × 5]&gt;
2 A     (all)  &lt;tibble [4 × 5]&gt;
3 A     a1     &lt;tibble [2 × 5]&gt;
4 A     a2     &lt;tibble [2 × 5]&gt;
5 B     (all)  &lt;tibble [4 × 5]&gt;
6 B     b1     &lt;tibble [1 × 5]&gt;
7 B     b2     &lt;tibble [2 × 5]&gt;
8 B     &lt;NA&gt;   &lt;tibble [1 × 5]&gt;



df1 |&gt;
  nest_by_with_margins(
    .margins = c(cat, subcat)
  )

# A tibble: 8 × 3
# Rowwise:  cat, subcat
  cat   subcat data            
  &lt;fct&gt; &lt;ord&gt;  &lt;list&gt;          
1 (all) (all)  &lt;tibble [8 × 5]&gt;
2 A     (all)  &lt;tibble [4 × 5]&gt;
3 A     a1     &lt;tibble [2 × 5]&gt;
4 A     a2     &lt;tibble [2 × 5]&gt;
5 B     (all)  &lt;tibble [4 × 5]&gt;
6 B     b1     &lt;tibble [1 × 5]&gt;
7 B     b2     &lt;tibble [2 × 5]&gt;
8 B     &lt;NA&gt;   &lt;tibble [1 × 5]&gt;


The data contained in each group is nested in the data column. This allows the same operation to be performed on each nested group at a time. See the followings for more information.

